notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger (Zacour-Hirsch). Title page is missing but an earlier (19th-century?) dealer's description (in Italian and French, translated by Zacour-Hirsch), tipped in between two preliminary leaves, provides the following information: "Poesie e prose spirituali, lettere ecc., written in the villa Quiete near Florence by Nicolò di Bar. Guidi, confessor of the Ancille della Quiete."

supportDesc.extent: 465 leaves : 191 x 137 (159 x 95) mm. bound to 200 x 155
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 465; 5-16, 1 unnumbered f., p. 21-928, 6 blank f. in contemporary hand, upper outer corner; p. 144-148 omitted in numeration with no loss of text.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand, with a few pasted-over and rewritten passages in a second hand.

binding.p: Velvet. Repairs on the first three leaves.

origin.p: Written in Florence, 1673 (date from missing title page supplied by dealer).
